<item>
            <title>[LU-18318] LNet: lnet routing between IPv6 tcp and o2ib lnets fails</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18318</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If lnet routing is set up to connect an IPv6-based tcp and an o2ib lnet, tcp and o2ib endpoints cannot reach each other.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
A &amp;lt;-o2ib-&amp;gt; R &amp;lt;-tcp (IPv6)-&amp;gt; B &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The nodes are able to add the proper routes and ping the router so that the route state is listed as &quot;up&quot; on both sides. However, &quot;lnetctl ping&quot; across the router times out.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
